15/07/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- On Monday (14 July), Foreign Minister Solomon Passy said Bulgaria's main priorities during its presidency of the OSCE will include boosting collaboration with NATO and the EU, as well as strengthening the OSCE's public image. Passy made the comments after meeting with OSCE Secretary General Jan Kubis. In turn, Kubis said that Bulgaria would have to meet new challenges in the field of regional security during its presidency. The country will assume the OSCE presidency in 2004. (BTA, BNT, Nova TV- 14/07/03)
